U.S. Open Tennis Singles Champions to Each Get Record $1.8 Million in 2011

-- B y   E r i k   M a t u s z e w s k i
-- 
2011-07-13T18:50:42Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-13/u-s-open-tennis-singles-champions-to-each-get-record-1-8-million-in-2011.html
The U.S. Open tennis singles
champions will each receive a record $1.8 million this year, an
increase of 6.4 percent from 2010.  The  season’s final major tournament  is scheduled for Aug.
29 to Sept. 11 in  New York  and features a record total purse of
$23.7 million, according to the U.S. Tennis Association.  Rafael Nadal and  Kim Clijsters  received $1.7 million each
after winning U.S. Open titles last year. This will be the 39th
straight year that the USTA offers equal prize money to the
men’s and women’s singles champions.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Erik Matuszewski in New York, at 
 matuszewski@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Michael Sillup at   msillup@bloomberg.net  